text.section:
The comprehensive management plan for the use of vessels on the Severn River and its tributaries shall include, but not necessarily be limited to:
Areas designated for specified uses;
Noise level limits of vessels;
Maximum speed limits of vessels;
Other limits that address water surface capacity and the safe operation of vessels so as to maximize the recreational and aesthetic values of the Severn River and its tributaries, consistent with sound environmental practices; and
A study of seaplane activity on the Severn River and its tributaries.
